<section xml:id="S_sporting_group">
  <title>Sporting Group</title>

  <subsection xml:id="SS_examples1">
    <title>Walk-Through Examples in <tag>p</tag></title>
    
  

  <p>
    For instance, you can type regular text! Yay sporting group dogs! 23! Ã©!
  </p>

  <p>
    This is math! <m>a^2 + b^2 = c^2</m> Yay!

    Next, let's look at displayed math!
    <me>
      \frac{1}{2} x = 2
    </me>
    <men xml:id="eqn-example1">
      \sqrt{4} = 2
    </men>

    <md>
      <mrow>\frac{1}{2} x \amp = 2</mrow>
      <mrow>2 * \frac{1}{2} x \amp = 2 * 2</mrow>
      <mrow>x \amp = 4</mrow>
    </md>

    <mdn>
      <mrow number="no"> \sqrt{10} \amp \ne 4</mrow>
      <mrow>\sqrt{25} \amp = 5</mrow>
    </mdn>
    
    
  </p>

  <p>
    In R, there are multiple packages that can be used such as <c>ggplot2</c> and <c>rmarkdown</c>. Moreover, you can install and import packages super quick!
    <cd>
      <cline>install.packages("ggplot2")</cline>
      <cline>library(ggplot2)</cline>
    </cd>
  </p>

  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="SS_examples2">
    <title>Pre-Made Examples in <tag>p</tag></title>

    <p>
      If you want a quote, use the <tag>q</tag> tag: Sporting group dogs are <q>Naturally active and alert</q> and <q>make likeable, well-rounded companions</q> (American Kennel Club). Blockquotes work too!
    </p>
    <blockquote>
      <p>
        Dogs are good friends.
      </p>
      <attribution>Unknown</attribution>
    </blockquote>
    
    <p>
      You can also make lists:
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Spaniels
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Pointers
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Retrievers
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Setters
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <ol>
        <li>
          <p>
            Find a dog you like
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Give it a name
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Play with it and love it forever
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <dl>
        <li>
          <title>Curly</title>
          <p>
            Dogs with curly fur have curls in their fur.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title>Short-Haired</title>
          <p>
            Short-haired dogs will have fur that is not long.
          </p>
        </li>
      </dl>
    </p>

    <p>
      Sometimes, you need to apply emphasis to words. You <em>can't</em> use italics or bold with <pretext /> but you <alert>can</alert> communicate based on a tone. Sorry, <foreign>c'est la vie</foreign>!
    </p>

    <p>
      Have you ever read <pubtitle>Dogs</pubtitle> by Lewis Blackwell and Tim Flach? It's all about dogs! If you need something shorter, try <articletitle>Dogs Are Even More Like Us Than We Thought</articletitle> from <url href="https://www.nationalgeographic.com/animals/article/150720-dogs-animals-science-pets-evolution-intelligence" visual="nationalgeographic.com/">National Geographic</url>. These resources are great.<fn>There are many more resources to read about dogs! You could even watch a documentary!</fn>
    </p>

    <p>
      Remember, this section is all about the Sporting Group. If you want to learn about the Toy Group, try <xref ref="S_toy_group"/>! In fact, all we have right now are two sections: Toy Group &amp; Sporting Group. We have sections planned for the rest of the groups and will be titled &lt;Group Name&gt; Group.
    </p>
    
  </subsection>

